FuncDef:
The active l2nat vsuf command activates the L2NAT service license on a VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E service board.
The undo active l2nat vsuf command deactivates the L2NAT service license on a VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E service board.
The license is inactive by default on the VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E service boards.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the slot ID of a service board.
The value is a string of 1 to 15 case-sensitive characters. It cannot contain spaces.

ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
Before using L2NAT, to activate the L2NAT service license on a service board, run the active l2nat vsuf command.
Prerequisites
A license file exists on the device.
